AB  - Since state-sanctioned racism has effectively been outlawed, Rich contends, we already have a post-racial society, and the media's emphasis on racial strife compounds our own failure to recognize this.In this complex and contemporary examination of American cultural attitudes toward race, Rich offers a series of lectures and essays that situate his topic in an historical timeline.In making his case that Americans resist the idea that we are already living in a post-racial society because of a focus on residual attitudes, Rich provides a useful generational structure for readers to consider.Furthermore, the current generation of Americans does not find race-based attitudes attractive, so the leaders of tomorrow will approach the future from a standpoint that does not include old prejudices.In summary, The Post-Racial Society Is Here by Wilbur C. Rich offers a compelling argument as to why Americans must recognize and embrace a cultural shift that, he contends, has already occurred.
